                     <interp inst="def1-989-18450407" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM HARRISON</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted for<rs id="t18450407-989-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18450407-989-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18450407-989-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp>stealing, on the <rs id="t18450407-cd-88" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18450407-989-offence-1 t18450407-cd-88"></join>19th of March</rs>, 1 watch, value 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18450407-name-1128" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1128" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1128" type="surname" value="PEARSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1128" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18450407-989-offence-1 t18450407-name-1128"></join>Samuel Pearson</persName>, in a vessel on the navigable river Thames; and</rs>
                  <persName id="def2-989-18450407" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-989-18450407" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-989-18450407" type="age" value="22"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-989-18450407" type="surname" value="CORMACK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-989-18450407" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN CORMACK</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18450407-989-offence-2" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18450407-989-offence-2" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18450407-989-offence-2" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp>, for feloniously receiving the same; well knowing it to have been stolen; to which</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">HARRISON</hi> pleaded <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18450407-989-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-989-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-989-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="pleadedGuilty"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 16.—<hi rend="italic">
                     <rs id="t18450407-989-punishment-166" type="punishmentDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-989-punishment-166" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-989-punishment-166" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>
                        <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-989-18450407 t18450407-989-punishment-166"></join>Confined Six Months</rs>.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1130" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1130" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1130" type="surname" value="PEARSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1130" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL PEARSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am mate of the brig <hi rend="italic">Union.</hi> On Thursday, the 20th of March, she was lying in Bugsby's-hole, below Blackwall—Harrison was an apprentice belonging to the ship—about ten minutes past four o'clock, on the 19th of March, I came ashore, leaving him in charge of the</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184504070200"></xptr>
               <p>cabin—I returned about five, and he was pone—I saw him no more till he was in custody—I directly missed my watch, which 1 had left hanging on the starboard side of the cabin—I have never seen it since.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1131" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1131" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1131" type="surname" value="SATCHELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1131" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE SATCHELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a seaman on board the <hi rend="italic">Union.</hi> On the Thursday morning after this I met Harrison in Church-lane, and gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1132" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1132" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1132" type="surname" value="BURKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1132" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BURKE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable H</hi> 81.) Harrison was given into my charge—he offered at the station-house to show me who he took the watch to if I took him to Cooper's-row—I did so, and Cormack was then appre<lb></lb>hended.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1133" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1133" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1133" type="surname" value="CONDON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1133" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CONDON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman.</hi>) I went with Harrison to No. 2, Cooper's-alley, and saw Cormack sitting in the house—Harrison said, "That is the man I sold the watch to"—Cormack said he knew nothing of the watch or Harrison—the boy Norton was there, and said, "It is no use denying it; I saw him buy the watch at the straw yard; he gave 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for it."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1134" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1134" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1134" type="surname" value="NORTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1134" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH NORTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I have been sleeping in the straw-yard in Ratcliff-highway—I know Cormack—he slept in the same place—I saw Harrison and him together on a Wednesday evening, just by the fire-place, and heard Harrison say to Cormack that he had a watch to sell him—Cormack told him to keep it till the morning, and he would look at it—Harrison asked him 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for it—Harrison slept in the straw-yard that night—next morning they came into the room where they sell coffee—I then saw the watch, and took it in my hand—it was silver, with a little steel chain, and a seal, marked, "One penny"—I saw Harrison sell it to Cormack for 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I saw the money pass—Cormack borrowed it from a man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cormack. Q.</hi> When did you see me with Harrison? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> On Wednesday night, just after they all went in—you borrowed the money of Joe Collier, who belongs to the Marine Society, and you paid him the money out of a sovereign.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">S</hi>. <hi rend="smallCaps">PEARSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> There was a steel chain to my watch, a key, and a seal with "One Penny" marked on the lower part of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">CORMACK</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18450407-989-verdict-2" type="verdictDescription">
